[1] Case updates
- Sat 13 Apr 2019. Epidemiological situation report, DRC Ministry of Health
[in French, machine trans., abridged, edited]
https://us13.campaign-archive.com/?u=89e5755d2cca4840b1af93176&id=cfa55c58ea

The epidemiological situation of the Ebola virus disease in the provinces of North Kivu and Ituri dated 12 Apr 2019:
- Since the beginning of the epidemic, the cumulative number of cases is 1240, of which 1174 are confirmed and 66 are probable. In total, there were 792 deaths (726 confirmed and 66 probable) and 365 people cured;
- 269 suspected cases are under investigation;
- 20 new confirmed cases, including 16 in Katwa, 1 in Vuhovi, 1 in Mandima, and 2 in Beni;
- 20 new confirmed case deaths, including 12 community deaths, including 10 in Katwa, 1 in Beni, and 1 in Mandima; 8 deaths at CTEs, including 5 in Katwa, 2 in Butembo, and 1 in Beni;
- The community death of Beni is a stillborn baby whose mother, a confirmed case, died at the CTE on 11 Apr [2019]. The baby died during the transfer of the mother to the CTE.
- 1 new healed from the CTE of Butembo.

News of the response

Vaccine efficacy study
--------------------
- The National Institute of Biomedical Research (INRB) and the World Health Organization (WHO) have published preliminary results of a study on the efficacy of the rVSV-ZEBOV-GP vaccine to control the Ebola outbreak. The objective of the study was to better understand if the vaccine was effective and help prevent the number of cases when used as part of the belt vaccination strategy. A more detailed analysis is being prepared and will be published in a scientific journal.
- The researchers analyzed the data of those vaccinated between 1 May 2018 and 25 Mar 2019. According to the data collected, the efficiency of the rVSV-GP-ZEBOV vaccine is estimated at 97.5%. These 1st results confirm previous observations on the very high efficacy of the rVSV-ZEBOV-GP against Ebola vaccine to control the spread of the epidemic. The belt vaccination strategy has been shown to be effective because of the rapid protection of those vaccinated after a single injection and the high coverage achieved in the different vaccination belts (91%).
- Of a sample of over 90 000 people vaccinated against Ebola, 71 developed the disease. Of these 71 people, 15 people developed the disease more than 10 days after vaccination, of which 7 were health workers. In this 1st group, no one died of Ebola. The other 56 people developed the 1st symptoms less than 10 days after being vaccinated, that is, before they could develop their immunity. It is estimated that the vaccine takes 10 days to offer maximum immune protection. In this 2nd group, 9 people died. This indicates that the vaccine has reduced the overall mortality rate among the vaccinated people who developed the disease.

Validation workshop of the implementation framework of the 3rd strategic response plan (SRP-3)
-----------------
- From 10-12 Apr 2019, minister of health Dr. Oly Ilunga Kalenga chaired a workshop on the validation of the implementation framework for SRP-3 in Goma. The objective of this workshop was to reframe the implementation of the SRP-3, focusing on 3 specific deliverables, namely to clarify the organizational chart of the response taking into account the new actors, to define a plan of action unique and inclusive by sub-coordination and pillar, as well as to develop an accountability and performance framework for all actors in the national and international response.
- As the minister of health has pointed out, the current Ebola outbreak is taking place in an extremely complex and challenging environment that requires a constant review of response strategies. He emphasized the importance of maintaining a healthy framework for consultation and collaboration among the many national and international organizations involved in this response to ensure the effectiveness of all interventions with greater community involvement.

Vaccination
--------
Since the beginning of the vaccination 8 Aug 2018, 98 966 people have been vaccinated. [See URL for numbers of vaccinees from each location. - Mod.LK]

