[The vaccine efficacy is impressive. Additional data are presented in the original report under "[3] vaccine" below. While the vaccine results are reason to be encouraged, sadly, this demonstrates that even a very effective vaccine alone is not sufficient to end this outbreak. Individuals who stay home when sick and die in community centers spread the virus to family members and unknown contacts who may not be identified in time to be vaccinated.

We look forward to more details on the strategic response plan 3, specifically clarification of the organizational chart of the response. Who are the new actors to whom the report refers? NGOs? What is the plan of action by sub-coordination and pillar? How will accountability and performance be measured for all actors in the national and international response? - Mod.LK]

